    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wooden boxes with slots where cutlery of various sizes is stored. These often bore decoration, and the more elaborate examples may exhibit exterior carving, marquetry, or inlays, and interiors lined with silk or velvet.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
